cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CE 

This paper discusses the use of web services in the context of the Virtual Observatory, which involves accessing and analyzing large amounts of astronomical data. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), software engineering (cs.SE), and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). However, given the focus on data access and interoperability, we believe cs.DL and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.IR, cs.SD (scientific data management), and cs.CE.
